  "body": "Using `setTimeout` in the 3+ arguments form:\r\n```js\r\nsetTimeout(handler: TimerHandler, timeout?: number, ...arguments: any[])\r\n```\r\nis not type-safe. If we ever change the function signature of the handler Typescript will not alert that these setTimeout calls are broken.\r\n\r\nI've found some uses of this pattern throughout the codebase.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/e71f29432f0a67b5ad467c88c4c6dcaab96fb2d5/packages/lodestar-validator/src/services/attestation.ts#L135-L139\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/e71f29432f0a67b5ad467c88c4c6dcaab96fb2d5/packages/lodestar/src/sync/utils/attestation-collector.ts#L64-L68\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/e71f29432f0a67b5ad467c88c4c6dcaab96fb2d5/packages/lodestar/src/tasks/tasks/interopSubnetsJoiningTask.ts#L78\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/e71f29432f0a67b5ad467c88c4c6dcaab96fb2d5/packages/lodestar/src/tasks/tasks/interopSubnetsJoiningTask.ts#L136-L144\r\n\r\nFind an alternative approach that ensures argument type-safety. Aren't class methods bind automatically?",
